cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS

This paper discusses the performance of binary classification algorithms, including those based on machine learning techniques, in the presence of adversarial manipulation of data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of classification algorithms in computer vision (cs.CV) and the importance of data statistics (cs.DS), which further support these sub-categories.
